Virtual appointments can be made through September 3, 2020 by clicking the link on our homepage. “Chromebook Requests.” You will be directed to our virtual scheduling calendar for Chromebook pick-up. 2) Remember to keep social distance, as appointments are made in 15 minute intervals.
3) You will be required to present Identification and sign off for your child’s (children) chromebook.
4) Once you have done that a chromebook will be assigned to you.
Thank you!

On Friday May 8, 2020 at 8:00 pm, the Milton L. Olive SSS team held a SEL Movie Night! We viewed this week's Flix Pix, "The Boy Who Harnessed The Wind". All scholars were invited during our LIVE SEL class earlier in the day and via our google classroom.
We had approximately 25 movie goers, all observed our established norms and were encouraged to complete the posted activity sheet regarding the movie. This movie was based on a true story and was a great example of the theme discussed today during our SEL classes - PERSEVERANCE.
The scholars suggested we do this every Friday night and as it fosters a stronger sense of community during these challenging times, we hope to oblige.

They have also donated masks to Islip, Brentwood, Bay shore, Central Islip and Est Islip School Districts.

post_text:
n an effort to be proactive and not disrupt the learning of our scholars, we have asked that teachers prepare grade level packets of academic work. Please note, these packets were designed as home instructional resources in the event our district has to cancel school for an extended period of time. At this time there is no need for your child to do anything with the packet as there are no plans to cancel school.

Your building principals have included additional information about the content of the packets that will help you and your child complete them in the event of a school closure. Teacher instructions have also been included to let students know their expectations regarding this packet. We will be posting these packets on our website in the new Virtual Backpack as PDF’s. This will allow you to make additional copies if needed. Please routinely check the Virtual Backpack for any updates and additional resources. If you have any questions please feel free to contact your child’s teacher and/or principal.

Thank you!

Dr. Gina Talbert, Acting Superintendent
